DTEND:20250917T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260313T190032Z
UID:4t7e0p85nkm38id8nkhq9hfrts@google.com
CREATED:20250828T143518Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>What’s &quot\;good” for audience metrics? It depends on the 
 stage of your publication’s lifecycle. This interactive training will help 
 you determine which key metrics to consider when measuring your success or 
 opportunities for growth\, whether your publication is just-launched or a f
 ew years old.<br><br>Tiny Vitals Coach and Journalist Sarah Day Owen Wiskir
 chen will draw on her first-hand knowledge as a former publisher of a local
  news startup\, Raleigh Convergence\, and audience analyst experience at ne
 wsrooms of all sizes in this workshop. She&#39\;ll share her reflections on
  using metrics to inform publishing decisions\, from the beginning to the e
 nd of her publication&#39\;s lifecycle\, and how she&#39\;d use them now. W
 e&#39\;ll explore how you can learn from your intended audience with pre-la
 unch actions and analytics from newsletters\, websites\, events\, social me
 dia\, and membership.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250828T143518Z
LOCATION:https://us06web.zoom.us/j/83930823601?pwd=V9maANJtMncGOvh8GHKa5Xoy
 jovU9L.1
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Tiny Vitals: My journey as a publisher through data — and what I'd 
 measure now
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
